Enyioha Opara, Minna Following attacks by gunmen in Galkogo and Zumba villages in the Shiroro Local Government Area of Niger State on Sunday, the personnel of the state police command, in conjunction with military personnel, have rescued five persons kidnapped by the gunmen. It was learnt that the gunmen, numbering over 60 and riding motorcycles, attacked the two communities in the early hours of Sunday and dispossessed the residents of their valuables. According to the villagers, the attack lasted more than three hours and threw the two communities into confusion. When contacted on the development, the Police Public Relations Officer in the state, Waisu Abiodun, confirmed that five abducted villagers had been rescued by the combined team of the police and military personnel. According to him, the command also deployed special squads to help tackle the challenge in the affected areas on the orders of the Commissioner of Police, Adamu Usman. The PPRO stated, “The Commissioner of Police, Adamu Usman, has since deployed special squads in the areas to help tackle the challenge and fish out the hoodlums making life unbearable for the residents of the two communities in Shiroro. “The operatives rescued five persons, who were earlier abducted by gunmen unhurt, while unfortunately, a riot police officer was killed in the process of exchanging gunfire with the hoodlums.” Abiodun added that with the presence of the Anti-Kidnapping Squad and the Anti-Terrorists Squad in the affected areas, the residents had started going back to their homes, as normalcy had returned to the areas.. Copyright PUNCH.
